AIG Warrants Fall to Record as Insurer Drops in Market Slump

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-08-18T19:16:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/aig-warrants-fall-to-record-as-insurer-drops-in-market-slump.html
American International Group Inc. (AIG) 
warrants dropped to the lowest since the contracts began trading
in January as the insurer fell in an equity-market slump.  The 10-year warrants, which allow investors to buy common
stock at $45 a share, plunged 89 cents, or 11 percent, to $6.90
at 3:06 p.m. in  New York . The insurer dropped 8.3 percent to
$22.78.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
